TY  - JOUR
TI  - The Stability of Edgeworth's Recontracting Process
AU  - Green, Jerry R.
AB  - [The core is the set of all unblocked allocations. Implicit in this definition is the idea that if an allocation is proposed which could be blocked, some coalition will form and issue a counterproposal which it can enforce. A process of successive counterproposals based on this idea is shown to converge in a finite period of time (amost surely) to the core.]
C1  - Full publication date: Jan., 1974
DB  - JSTOR
DO  - 10.2307/1913682
EP  - 34
IS  - 1
PB  - [Wiley, Econometric Society]
PY  - 1974
